column5: Hey guys,  Finally my lake is frozen over and to my suprise there is almost 8" of ice. I went out for an hour before dark tonight and drilled 15 or so holes in one of the bays. I located fish but couldn't get them to bite. I plan on getting out on an old stand by spot around first light we will see what happens. I will keep you guys posted..
Awesome Curtis,  lookin' forward to many more ice reports
Do you live on Crowe Lake?
no im on a private lake.. its only 45acres.. bass, perch, sunfish n bullheads..
